gi|6323074: note:Microtubule polymerase of the XMAP215/Dis1 family; required for elongation of mitotic spindle during anaphase, as well as for spindle orientation and metaphase chromosome alignment; stabilizes or destabilizes kinetochore-microtubule attachment depending on kinetochore tension; interacts with spindle pole body component Spc72p; metazoan ch-TOG/XMAP215 family member

gi|10383811: DEFINITION:CCR4-NOT core subunit CDC39 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6323866: DEFINITION:putative carboxylic ester hydrolase [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6321552: DEFINITION:chromatin-remodeling histone chaperone SPT6 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6324157: Anaphase-promoting complex (APC), subunit 1 (meiotic check point regulator/Tsg24)

gi|6322951: note:Ubiquitin-specific protease; cleaves ubiquitin from ubiquitinated proteins; UBP11 has a paralog, UBP7, that arose from the whole genome duplication

gi|6323194: note:Pseudouridine synthase; catalyzes only the formation of pseudouridine (Psi)-2819 in mitochondrial 21S rRNA; not essential for viability

gi|6324530: DEFINITION:bifunctional N-glycosylase/AP lyase NTG2 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6322032: Rho GTPase effector BNI1 and related formins

gi|6320780: Predicted regulator of rRNA gene transcription (MYB-binding protein)

gi|6323874: DEFINITION:transport protein particle complex II subunit TRS130 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6319890: note:TFIID subunit (150 kDa); involved in RNA polymerase II transcription initiation

gi|6325290: note:Cytoplasmic and mitochondrial histidine tRNA synthetase; efficient mitochondrial localization requires both a presequence and an amino-terminal sequence; mutations in human ortholog HARS2 are associated with Perrault syndrome
gi|6320313: Protein with predicted involvement in meiosis (GSG1)

gi|6322634: note:5-oxoprolinase; enzyme is ATP-dependent and functions as a dimer; similar to mouse Oplah gene; green fluorescent protein (GFP)-fusion protein localizes to the cytoplasm; protein abundance increases in response to DNA replication stress
gi|6322766: note:Zinc-binding mitochondrial intermembrane space (IMS) protein; involved in a disulfide relay system for IMS import of cysteine-containing proteins; binds Mia40p and stimulates its Erv1p-dependent oxidation, probably by sequestering zinc
gi|6320396: DEFINITION:RuvB family ATP-dependent DNA helicase pontin [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:ATP-dependent DNA helicase, also known as pontin; member of the AAA+ and RuvB-like protein families; similar to Rvb2p; conserved component of multiple complexes including the INO80 complex, the Swr1 complex, and the R2TP complex (Rvb1-Rvb2-Tah1-Pih1); involved in multiple processes such as chromatin remodeling, box C/D snoRNP assembly, and RNA polymerase II assembly
gi|6324925: note:Tubulin folding factor D involved in beta-tubulin (Tub2p) folding; isolated as mutant with increased chromosome loss and sensitivity to benomyl; CIN1 mRNA level is reduced when downstream gene MNE1 is deleted
gi|6323280: Peroxisomal membrane protein MPV17 and related proteins

note:Protein required for ethanol metabolism; induced by heat shock and localized to the inner mitochondrial membrane; lysine auxotroph proposed to function in pyrimidine metabolism; homologous to mammalian peroxisomal membrane protein Mpv17; human homolog MPV17 is implicated in hepatocerebral mtDNA depletion syndromes (MDDS), and complements yeast null mutant
gi|6324866: Peroxisomal membrane protein MPV17 and related proteins
note:hypothetical protein; green fluorescent protein (GFP)-fusion protein localizes to the vacuole; YOR292C is not an essential gene
gi|6323889: RNA polymerase I transcription factor UAF

note:Non-essential sumoylated hypothetical protein; similar to components of human SWI/SNF complex including SMRD3; green fluorescent protein (GFP)-fusion protein localizes to the cytoplasm, nucleus and nucleolus; TRI1 has a paralog, UAF30, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6324869: RNA polymerase I transcription factor UAF

note:Subunit of UAF (upstream activation factor) complex; UAF is an RNA polymerase I specific transcription stimulatory factor composed of Uaf30p, Rrn5p, Rrn9p, Rrn10p, histones H3 and H4; targeting factor for the UAF that facilitates activation of many rDNA genes; deletion decreases cellular growth rate; UAF30 has a paralog, TRI1, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6319634: Leucine rich repeat proteins, some proteins contain F-box

note:Modulator of cell separation and mitotic exit; inhibits separation through Ub-dependent Ace2p proteolysis; part of a daughter-specific switch induced by the mitotic exit network that inhibits exit and resets the cell cycle after the execution of MEN function, blocking Tem1p and Cdc15 association; required for chromosome stability and multiple mitotic checkpoints; regulated by SCF; haploid transcription regulated by Ste12p; contains 12 degenerate leucine-rich repeat motifs and an atypical F-box
